Use Roblox version string as bundle identifier; auto-replace old bundles

User asked to drop the integer version field from manual uploads, use
the Roblox version name (e.g. "version-2e6461290a3541f5") as the
bundle identity, and have any new upload (manual or automated) replace
the previous bundle so only one is ever kept.

Changes:
- /api/roblox_bundle/info now returns the Roblox version string from
  the bundle's note field as `version` when it matches
  ^version-[a-f0-9]{8,}$, falling back to the integer otherwise. The
  launcher already does string equality on this value, so existing
  clients re-download once and then cache the new identifier.
- Manual upload form (/roblox_bundles): removed the "Version (integer)"
  input. Now there is just one text field labelled "Roblox version"
  (the existing note column) plus the file picker. Server auto-assigns
  MAX(version)+1 internally to keep the UNIQUE INDEX happy.
- Manual upload paths (/roblox_bundles POST and /roblox_bundles/upload_raw)
  now prune to BUNDLE_RETENTION_COUNT after every upload, matching the
  automated /api/admin/upload_bundle behaviour. Previously manual
  uploads were exempt from pruning. With BUNDLE_RETENTION_COUNT default
  of 1, every new upload replaces the existing bundle.
- Renamed the "Update Roblox bundle now" button + section header to
  "Update bundles".

Architect review uncovered a real bug: when the same Roblox version is
uploaded twice the filename collides (filename derived from note), so
naive prune would delete the file shared by the surviving DB row.
Fixed by:
- Switching os.rename -> os.replace so the second upload atomically
  overwrites the in-place file on both POSIX and Windows.
- Extracting prune logic into _prune_to_retention(conn, n) which
  deletes the row first, then only removes the file if no surviving
  row still references that filename.

Verified end-to-end:
- Different-version uploads: old file removed cleanly.
- Same-version uploaded twice: file overwritten in place, older DB row
  pruned, file remains on disk for the active row.

Bundle update + history hardening (architect review fixes)
- Race-safe collision rollback: when INSERT hits IntegrityError after
  os.replace, only delete dest if no surviving DB row still references
  that filename. Same-version uploads share a path; blind os.remove(dest)
  could orphan the winning row's download. Applied to both
  _ingest_bundle_from_stream and /api/admin/upload_bundle.
- /api/admin/bundle_status now calls _reconcile_bundles_dir first so the
  unattended builder sees an accurate "current" bundle even if a .zip
  vanished from disk.
- _reconcile_bundles_dir auto-import is now strict: skips .upload_* and
  hidden files, requires the canonical roblox_bundle_v<int>... name, and
  zipfile-validates the archive + checks for RobloxPlayerBeta.exe before
  registering. Prevents bad/junk zips dropped in BUNDLES_DIR from being
  served as the live bundle.

Verified:
- History page (/history and /api/history_data) shows revoked AND deleted
  licenses for both trial and premium with correct badges and trial tag.
- bundle_status self-heals ghost rows whose .zip file is missing.
- Junk .zip placed in bundles dir is NOT auto-imported.
- A correctly-named bundle containing RobloxPlayerBeta.exe IS imported.
